LANCASTER COUNTY SOLID WASTE MANAGEMENT AUTHORITY REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Lancaster County Solid Waste Management Authority ("LCSWMA") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from the Lancaster Waste-to-Energy and Susquehanna Resource Management Complex facilities located near Lancaster, Pennsylvania that are interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth LCSWMA's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the facilities pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $340,000.00.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $340,000.00 / 12 = $28,333.33.
The annual revenue requirement is divided between the Lancaster Waste-to-Energy Facility ("WTE Facility") and the Susquehanna Resource Management Complex ("SRMC") as follows:
WTE Facility - $265,200.00
SRMC - $74,800.00
